The most common technique for determining the oxygen environment (e.g., bridging vs. terminal) in hepta-valent neptunium (Np(VII)) compounds is **X-ray absorption spectroscopy (XAS)**, particularly **extended X-ray absorption fine structure (EXAFS)** or **X-ray absorption near edge structure (XANES)**.

\boxed{\text{X-ray absorption spectroscopy (XAS)}}

This method provides detailed local structural information around the neptunium center, including bond lengths, coordination numbers, and ligand environments. It is widely used for actinide chemistry due to its sensitivity to oxidation states and bonding geometry.
